g.title: j323758594
g.text: Hey, Eleanor. How are you doing?

g.title: j724100610
g.text: Spiffing. Just been shaving my tongue.

g.title: j2459004657
g.text: Shaving?

g.title: j1349969122
g.text: Hold up. *What?*

g.title: j288697497
g.text: Shaving. These nobbly bits keep sprouting out of it. I think they used to be taste buds. If I don’t slice them off, they get really long and squirmy. Like a sea anemone.

g.title: j339625280
g.text: It's really no different from trimming one's nails.

g.title: j1202026596
g.text: Sorry. I really should have warned you about this.

g.title: j1327208542
g.text: Messier, perhaps. But still nothing more than the paring back of an unwanted excrescence.

g.title: j84024574
g.text: Everybody else knows to be at least a hundred yards away when Eleanor heads into the bathrooms with a kitchen knife and a bottle of surgical alcohol.

g.title: j1418399656
g.text: Just wait patiently and eventually I’ll come back out with blood all down my chin and a plastic bag of stuff like crab meat in my hand. I tried to turn the offcuts into burgers once but nobody wanted any.

g.title: j832210704
g.text: Sorry, did you want the half hour erotic chat experience or just the five minutes?

g.title: j2028622340
g.text: Stop trying to gross me out.

g.title: j1164305279
g.text: So, while we're talking about the tongue...

g.title: j627014775
g.text: Oi. I’m the one with half an eel down my trachea. Pardon me for trying to joke about it.

g.title: j1726127944
g.text: Go on.

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j1450090207
g.text: ... how much control have you got over it?

g.title: j829040513
g.text: Right. Wait a moment.

g.title: j1626369834
g.text: thids much

g.title: j816133498
g.text: howm i dioing

g.title: j4267582744
g.text: Tell me you're not.

g.title: j624007016
g.text: Oh, hell no. I'm out. [End.]

g.title: j762728902
g.text: o but i amm hheehhe

g.title: j431444028
g.text: You’re typing with it?!

g.title: j3016987159
g.text: Pardon me if this is too personal but... what *else* can you do with it...?

g.title: j1391729114
g.text: mmm

g.title: j3404540633
g.text: welll

g.title: j1918539362
g.text: But not for long though because I get saliva all over the keyboard.

g.title: j1952318976
g.text: thnk abot what you wld do

g.title: j3673830258
g.text: Anyway. Now you know.

g.title: j2697485424
g.text: me too

g.title: j2884612390
g.text: Do you ever lose control of it?

g.title: j438745583
g.text: Do you ever bite it by accident?

g.title: j1788761515
g.text: feels gooood hehe

g.title: j2350957082
g.text: Damnnable thing does seem to have a mind of its own. When I think about it, I can control it. But when I'm not, it seems to react to my emotions.

g.title: j3649256275
g.text: All the time. It heals fast.

g.title: j1548558611
g.text: Boolean EleanorFlirt is now true.

g.title: j3362289611
g.text: The more horrid possibility is that its driven not by ME but by my latent connection to the Techrot. I'd rather not consider that option.

g.title: j4289174432
g.text: The one and only time I ever bit it off completely, it grew back. I’m stuck with this thing.

g.title: j2866291714
g.text: I. Heh. Well, then. I guess my next question would be... do you ever lose control of it?

g.title: j893542690
g.text: I do hate it when it gets in the way of my teeth, however. The one and only time I ever bit it off completely, it grew back. I'm stuck with this thing.

g.title: j589459444
g.text: At least it’s not getting any longer. Just putting out frondy bits.

g.title: j392089593
g.text: Would you want to go back to the way you used to be before Entrati changed you?

g.title: j3271256704
g.text: How do you feel about it? Like... really feel about it?

g.title: j3768034903
g.text: I mean, yes? In a heartbeat. But I can’t, so what’s the point of dwelling on it?

g.title: j3175846129
g.text: I wouldn't have chosen it. But I don't hate it. It feels like it's always been there.

g.title: j3571707657
g.text: Everything that happens to us happens for a reason.

g.title: j3058030969
g.text: I miss the sound of my own voice. I hate that I can't sing any more.

g.title: j554039967
g.text: Yeah. It’s just that sometimes the reason is: an evil bastard did something evil.

g.title: j399014262
g.text: But the tongue? You might find this hard to believe, but it's comforting sometimes. I'll never be unarmed ever again.

g.title: j1572533356
g.text: So if you’re saying that everything always works out for the best, like there’s some great plan or purpose to it all, then you’re on your own. I don’t buy into that.

g.title: j2877959701
g.text: So… what do you like most about being like you are now?

g.title: j1940345496
g.text: I'm glad at least ONE of you is trying to find a silver lining...

g.title: j2507987141
g.text: Check boolean EleanorHeroVirus

g.title: j3878509349
g.text: Feeling indestructible.

g.title: j2010125913
g.text: Only one? Have you MET Amir?

g.title: j717935920
g.text: It’s hero virus stuff. You end up thinking you’re the main character in everyone else’s story.

g.title: j2507987141->j717935920
g.text: true

g.title: j3542139722
g.text: There’s no great story here, mate. No author in the sky adding little plot beats to my life for dramatic effect.

g.title: j2507987141->j3542139722
g.text: false

g.title: j79210578
g.text: Mind if I tell you a story?

g.title: j1309087047
g.text: He has his dark moments, but that boy is an inspiration to us all.

g.title: j431071951
g.text: I get to make meaning out of the stupid shit that happens to me. I’m the artist, not Sol or Lua or any of the stars in between.

g.title: j2280150756
g.text: Go ahead.

g.title: j665668744
g.text: Compared to mooching about with a face like a slapped arse, I'll take Amir's attitude any day.

g.title: j3106372514
g.text: Check boolean EleanorGalvanized

g.title: j369810564
g.text: When I was eighteen, a whole bunch of us had been out celebrating the end of the exams. We were all packed into this tiny car. Me lying across three people’s laps on the back seat.

g.title: j1933300832
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j3177025978
g.text: You reminded me of that. I don’t know if you even remember. I was feeling sorry for myself and you snapped me out of it.

g.title: j3106372514->j3177025978
g.text: true

g.title: j3171209934
g.text: Glad I could help.

g.title: j3106372514->j3171209934
g.text: false

g.title: j3051285917
g.text: You’re not saying that life is meaningless, are you?

g.title: j3106372514->j3051285917
g.text: false

g.title: j2864660240
g.text: Seb Cromley in the boot, whingeing. Christopher and Marco in the front. Every one of us was drunk off our arse on strawberry vodka and ratcatcher.

g.title: j3525092946
g.text: Gods, no. I’m saying that meaning is under the surface and it takes a sculptor’s chisel to get to it.

g.title: j3273507987
g.text: Marco ran a red light, a car coming the other way T-boned us, we rolled off the road and ended up in a ditch. I only know that because that’s what the policeman told me had happened.

g.title: j3942871944
g.text: Some days it all feels bleak, horrible and hollow and I don’t want to get off the couch. But when I’m back to myself again, I know that feeling was a lie.

g.title: j1847661709
g.text: They had to cut me out of the car. I wouldn’t stop screaming. It was the kind of hurt that leaves you with no crevice anywhere in yourself to crawl into to get away from it. You're being punished for existing.

g.title: j3331043049
g.text: Nobody else holds the keys to meaning, you know? It’s a jam session between you and the universe. She throws stuff at you, you improvise around it.

g.title: j1959571352
g.text: I was helpless as a baby rabbit. Melted like a crayon. Gone. Just lay there and belted out scream after scream. I’d always thought of myself as a tough cookie before that.

g.title: j1908767431
g.text: It helps to focus on the parts of being semi-infested that I really like.

g.title: j1837881108
g.text: Boolean EleanorCrash is now true.

g.title: j4144082985
g.text: I know the kind of pain you mean.

g.title: j439375743
g.text: Two days ago I was run over by a Scaldra APC.

g.title: j1784347441
g.text: That same old pain went flooding through me, but it wasn’t crippling any more. It was like fuel, revving me up, making me angry.

g.title: j3945932834
g.text: I picked myself up, relocated my shoulder and tore that APC open with my bare hands.

g.title: j1111750098
g.text: Agonizing, yes. But intoxicating.

g.title: j1998240984
g.text: +20 Chemistry

g.title: j1670812793
g.text: So yeah, thanks for that much, Entrati. Wherever you are.
